description: Retrieves entries from a fleet's event log. Fleet events are initiated by changes in status, such as during fleet creation and termination, changes in capacity, etc. If a fleet has multiple locations, events are also initiated by changes to status and capacity in remote locations. You can specify a time range to limit the result set. Use the pagination parameters to retrieve results as a set of sequential pages. If successful, a collection of event log entries matching the request are returned. Setting up Amazon GameLift fleets.

parameters.name: FleetId
parameters.description: A unique identifier for the fleet to get event logs for. You can use either the fleet ID or ARN value.

nested_items.name: Events
nested_items.description: A collection of objects containing event log entries for the specified fleet.

nested_items.name: EventId
nested_items.description: A unique identifier for a fleet event.

nested_items.name: ResourceId
nested_items.description: A unique identifier for an event resource, such as a fleet ID.

nested_items.name: EventCode
nested_items.description: The type of event being logged.
FLEET_CREATED --- A fleet resource was successfully created with a status of NEW. Event messaging includes the fleet ID.
FLEET_STATE_DOWNLOADING --- Fleet status changed from NEW to DOWNLOADING. Amazon GameLift is downloading the compressed build and running install scripts.
FLEET_STATE_VALIDATING --- Fleet status changed from DOWNLOADING to VALIDATING. Amazon GameLift has successfully installed build and is now validating the build files.
FLEET_STATE_BUILDING --- Fleet status changed from VALIDATING to BUILDING. Amazon GameLift has successfully verified the build files and is now launching a fleet instance.

FLEET_STATE_ACTIVATING --- Fleet status changed from BUILDING to ACTIVATING. Amazon GameLift is launching a game server process on the fleet instance and is testing its connectivity with the Amazon GameLift service.
FLEET_STATE_ACTIVE --- The fleet's status changed from ACTIVATING to ACTIVE. The fleet is now ready to host game sessions.
FLEET_STATE_ERROR --- The Fleet's status changed to ERROR. Describe the fleet event message for more details.

nested_items.name: Message
nested_items.description: Additional information related to the event.

nested_items.name: EventTime
nested_items.description: Time stamp indicating when this event occurred. Format is a number expressed in Unix time as milliseconds (for example "1469498468.057").

nested_items.name: PreSignedLogUrl
nested_items.description: Location of stored logs with additional detail that is related to the event. This is useful for debugging issues. The URL is valid for 15 minutes. You can also access fleet creation logs through the Amazon GameLift console.

nested_items.name: Count
nested_items.description: The number of times that this event occurred.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: A token that indicates where to resume retrieving results on the next call to this operation. If no token is returned, these results represent the end of the list.
